        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 12:57PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1257 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Trinchera, or 17 miles northeast of Raton, moving east
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Branson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
